Adding html pages to Fusebase

1. Click + (new) > New Repository
2. Enter the name of the how-to or html file
3. Click "Add a README file"
4. Click "Create Repository"
5. Click "Add file" > Upload files
6. Select the files within the extracted zip folder and drag them into Github
7. Click "Commit changes"
8. Click "Settings"
9. Click "Pages"
10. Click "None" and change to "main" > /root > Save
10.1.
11. Copy the website link that was created
12. On Fusebase page > Paste the URL > Click "embed"
13. Resize as needed
